[
  "div",
  {
    "className": "content-wrapper"
  },
  [
    "h1",
    {},
    "Groups of Verbs"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    "In Greek, verbs are categorized into \"Conjugations\" (Συζυγίες) based on their ending in the Present Tense. Knowing which group a verb belongs to is essential for conjugating it correctly."
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "content-grid mt-8"
    }
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "content-card first"
    },
    [
      "h3",
      {},
      "First Conjugation"
    ],
    [
      "p",
      {},
      [
        "-ω (unaccented)Verbs ending in ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "-ω"
        ],
        " where the accent is on the stem."
      ]
    ],
    [
      "ul",
      {
        "className": "phrase-list"
      },
      [
        "li",
        {},
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "spanish"
          },
          "τρέχω"
        ],
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "meaning"
          },
          "I run"
        ]
      ],
      [
        "li",
        {},
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "spanish"
          },
          "παίζω"
        ],
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "meaning"
          },
          "I play"
        ]
      ]
    ]
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "content-card second"
    },
    [
      "h3",
      {},
      "Second Conjugation"
    ],
    [
      "p",
      {},
      [
        "-ώ (accented)Verbs ending in ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "-ώ"
        ],
        " where the accent is on the last syllable."
      ]
    ],
    [
      "ul",
      {
        "className": "phrase-list"
      },
      [
        "li",
        {},
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "spanish"
          },
          "αγαπώ"
        ],
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "meaning"
          },
          "I love"
        ]
      ],
      [
        "li",
        {},
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "spanish"
          },
          "νικώ"
        ],
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "meaning"
          },
          "I win"
        ]
      ]
    ]
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "content-card passive"
    },
    [
      "h3",
      {},
      "Middle/Passive"
    ],
    [
      "p",
      {},
      [
        "-όμαι / -άμαιVerbs ending in ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "-μαι"
        ],
        ". These often have a reflexive or passive meaning."
      ]
    ],
    [
      "ul",
      {
        "className": "phrase-list"
      },
      [
        "li",
        {},
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "spanish"
          },
          "κάθομαι"
        ],
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "meaning"
          },
          "I sit"
        ]
      ],
      [
        "li",
        {},
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "spanish"
          },
          "κοιμάμαι"
        ],
        [
          "span",
          {
            "className": "meaning"
          },
          "I sleep"
        ]
      ]
    ]
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "info-box mt-12"
    },
    [
      "h3",
      {},
      "Why the Accent Matters"
    ],
    [
      "p",
      {},
      [
        "The accent mark on the final ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "-ώ"
        ],
        " tells you that the verb follows a different set of endings (often adding an extra -α- in the conjugation)."
      ]
    ],
    [
      "p",
      {},
      [
        "Example: 1st Group ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "τρέχ-εις"
        ],
        " vs 2nd Group ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "αγαπ-άς"
        ],
        "."
      ]
    ]
  ]
]